<!-- FAQ FOR TEMPLATE -->

   <FAQs 
  id="faqtemplate"
  tagline="FAQ"
  title="PIA Template"
  subtitle=""
  columns={1}
  items={[
      {
        title: 'How does The Privacy Pro PIA Template compare to OneTrust, TrustArc, and other tools?',
        description: 'The Privacy Pro PIA Template is a lightweight, Excel-based alternative to privacy management software like OneTrust or TrustArc. It is faster to deploy, easier to adapt, and designed to reflect how privacy works in practice within real organizations.<br><br>Instead of following a checklist for each law, it focuses on helping teams make informed decisions, document risks clearly, and align with internal business processes.', 
      },
       {
        title: 'Is the PIA Template suitable for AI or advanced data processing use cases?',
        description: 'Yes. The PIA Template supports emerging privacy challenges, including artificial intelligence, machine learning, and automated decision-making. It helps teams consider the use of AI and other advanced technologies in the business context in which they are used.', 
      },
      {
        title: 'What industries use The Privacy Pro PIA Template?',
        description: 'The PIA Template is used across industries in the private sector including technology, finance, retail, entertainment, e-commerce, and nonprofit sectors. It works for companies in both regulated and unregulated industries that need to identify privacy risks and comply with data protection laws.', 
      },
      {
        title: 'Is the PIA Template a software tool?',
        description: 'No. The Privacy Pro PIA Template is an Excel-based tool, not a software application. It requires no logins, no onboarding, and no configuration. It is designed for immediate use by teams who want a simple and effective way to manage privacy risks.', 
      },      
      {
        title: 'I work in a large organization. Is an Excel workbook going to be enough for us?',
        description: 'Yes, especially at the beginning. Large companies often use the Excel-based PIA Template to define their privacy workflows before investing in software. This allows teams to test processes, align on business needs, and avoid building around tools that may not fit.', 
      },
      {
        title: 'What if we already have a PIA Tool?',
        description: 'Many of our clients use software tools but choose the Privacy Pro PIA Template to fill gaps or simplify their process. The template can be used on its own or alongside platforms like OneTrust or TrustArc, especially when software is too complex or time consuming to configure.', 
      },
      {
        title: 'Can I see the PIA Template before I purchase it?',
        description: 'Of course! Feel free to send a message or book a call.', 
      },
      {
        title: 'How often is the PIA Template updated?',
        description: 'As often as it needs to be! Our goal is to update it as infrequently as possible. As new privacy laws are introduced, we have added questions or clarifying guidance. As of today, we are on PIA Template v2.0.', 
      },
    ]}
   />

  <!-- FAQ FOR TRAINING -->

<FAQs 
