      },
      {
        title:'Is the PIA Workshop suitable for beginners?',
        description: 'Yes, the PIA training is designed for privacy professionals at all levels. While a basic understanding of privacy principles (such as data minimization, purpose limitation, or lawful basis) is helpful, we adapt the training to meet your team where they are. It’s practical, hands-on, and grounded in real-world privacy risk scenarios.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Can we invite our vendor, partner, consultant, or outside counsel to join the workshop?',
        description: 'Generally, our Privacy Impact Assessment Workshops are designed for internal teams from the same organization, including long-term contractors. This allows for open discussion and alignment on privacy risk, compliance responsibilities, and decision-making. If you would like to include a trusted third party, let us know, we are open to case-by-case exceptions.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Who teaches the PIA Workshop?',
        description: 'Workshops are led by Lauren Reid, Founder and CEO of The Privacy Pro, and the creator of the Privacy Pro PIA Template. With 20+ years of global experience in privacy, compliance, and risk, Lauren brings practical insight and deep expertise to every training session.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Can The Privacy Pro come to our offices?',
        description: 'Yes! While we offer most training virtually, we are happy to deliver the PIA Workshop in person for clients who prefer onsite collaboration. In-person workshops can create stronger team alignment and more dynamic discussion which is especially useful for complex or cross-functional teams.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Can I get a preview of the case studies used in training?',
        description: 'Yes. We’re happy to share a brief overview of the case studies we use in our workshops, including topics like location data in mobile apps, AI in hiring, and B2B sales workflows. These scenarios reflect real-world privacy challenges and are designed to help your team navigate uncertainty, competing priorities, and risk tradeoffs.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Do we get access to the PIA template after the workshop?',
        description: 'The standard PIA Workshop does not include the Privacy Pro PIA Template by default, but it is available as an optional add-on. If you would like your team to continue using the same tool after training, let us know and we will include a quote with the appropriate licensing and customization options.',
      },
    ]}
